**Special Containment Procedures:** SCP-6437 is to be housed in standard anomalous human housing on Site-357. Measures are to be taken to minimize SCP-6437's contact with and knowledge of criticisms directed at non-conventional art forms. Psychiatric care is to be provided to SCP-6437 in the form of biweekly therapy and anger counseling sessions by licensed Foundation therapists.

**Description:** SCP-6437 is "Archer Gilliam", a low profile anartist with a number of connections in noted anartist circles. SCP-6437 has a tendency to incur a great amount of stress when encountering discussions relating to what qualifies as art. When this stress grows to a great enough level, an SCP-6437-A instance is manifested targeting the art piece that SCP-6437 is feeling most strongly about in that moment.

SCP-6437-A instances are a collection of miscellaneous bullets.  Instances have shown no additional anomalous properties following their manifestation.

**Addendum-6437.1:** 

[[div class="blockquote"]]

= **Incident 12/07/2023-6437**
----
**Location:** Site-357

**Event:** During an an interrogation with SCP-6437, Junior Researcher Turner Flock engaged in a line of questioning that caused the subject's abilities to activate. In contrast to previous manifestation events, this caused a file named "SCP-6437-A.txt" to be downloaded onto Site-357's data storage systems. Along side this, files named "Is_It_Art_Yet?.png" were addended to 78% of SCP files housed on the server. Due to this sudden download, safeguard procedures activated, shutting down the Site's data storage infrastructure for 14 Hours.
[[/div]]
